---
import AdBanner from '../../components/banner/AdBanner';
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout 
  name="PNG Icons Credits"
  path="/png_icons/credits"
  title="PNG Icons Credits & Acknowledgments | Online Free DevTools by Hexmos"
  description="Credits and acknowledgments for the free PNG icons available on Free DevTools. Learn about the sources, licenses, and contributors."
  canonical="https://hexmos.com/freedevtools/png_icons/credits/"
  themeColor="#1e40af"
  showSidebar={false}
  showHeader={true}
>
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-2 md:px-6">
    <div class="mb-16 mt-[74px]">
      <AdBanner />
    </div>
    
    <div class="mb-8">
      <nav class="text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 mb-4">
        <a href="/freedevtools/" class="hover:text-blue-600 dark:hover:text-blue-400">Free DevTools</a>
        <span class="mx-2">/</span>
        <a href="/freedevtools/png_icons/" class="hover:text-blue-600 dark:hover:text-blue-400">PNG Icons</a>
        <span class="mx-2">/</span>
        <span>Credits</span>
      </nav>
      
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-100 mb-4">
        PNG Icons Credits & Acknowledgments
      </h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 mb-6">
        We thank the creators and contributors who have made these free PNG icons possible.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="prose prose-slate dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
      <h2>Icon Sources</h2>
      <p>
        The PNG icons available on Free DevTools are sourced from various open-source projects and contributors. 
        We are committed to providing proper attribution and ensuring all icons are used in compliance with their respective licenses.
      </p>

      <h2>License Information</h2>
      <p>
        Most icons are available under open-source licenses such as:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>MIT License</strong> - Permits commercial and non-commercial use with attribution</li>
        <li><strong>Apache 2.0</strong> - Permits commercial and non-commercial use with attribution</li>
        <li><strong>Creative Commons</strong> - Various CC licenses with different requirements</li>
        <li><strong>Public Domain</strong> - No restrictions on use</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Contributing Icons</h2>
      <p>
        We welcome contributions of high-quality PNG icons. If you have icons you'd like to contribute, please ensure they:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Are original works or properly licensed for redistribution</li>
        <li>Are in PNG format with clean, scalable code</li>
        <li>Include appropriate metadata (name, description, category, tags)</li>
        <li>Follow consistent styling and naming conventions</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Icon Categories</h2>
      <p>
        Our icons are organized into the following categories:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>General</strong> - Common icons for various purposes</li>
        <li><strong>Animals</strong> - Animal-themed icons and illustrations</li>
        <li><strong>Nature</strong> - Nature and environmental icons</li>
        <li><strong>Technology</strong> - Tech and software-related icons</li>
        <li><strong>Business</strong> - Business and professional icons</li>
        <li><strong>Social</strong> - Social media and communication icons</li>
        <li><strong>Shapes</strong> - Basic geometric shapes and patterns</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Usage Guidelines</h2>
      <p>
        When using these icons in your projects:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Check the specific license for each icon</li>
        <li>Provide appropriate attribution when required</li>
        <li>Respect the original creator's rights</li>
        <li>Use icons in a manner consistent with their intended purpose</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        If you have questions about icon licensing, want to report an issue, or have suggestions for improvement, 
        please contact us through our main website or GitHub repository.
      </p>

      <h2>Special Thanks</h2>
      <p>
        We extend our gratitude to all the designers, developers, and contributors who have created and shared 
        these wonderful icons with the community. Your work makes it possible for developers around the world 
        to create beautiful and functional applications.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Back Navigation -->
    <div class="mt-10 pt-6 mb-8 border-t border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-700">
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4">
        <a 
          href="/freedevtools/png_icons/" 
          class="inline-flex items-center px-4 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400 bg-blue-50 dark:bg-blue-900/20 rounded-lg hover:bg-blue-100 dark:hover:bg-blue-900/30 transition-colors"
        >
          ‚Üê  Back to PNG Icons
        </a>
        <a 
          href="/freedevtools/" 
          class="inline-flex items-center px-4 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 bg-slate-50 dark:bg-slate-800 rounded-lg hover:bg-slate-100 dark:hover:bg-slate-700 transition-colors"
        >
          Free DevTools Home
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
